{"pageModel":{"attributes":{"id":"","name":"129803.dita","viewName":"DitaDetail"},"elements":{"ditaContent":{"name":"DITAContent","value":"<article id=\"about-mulit-organizations-in-security-cloud-control\" class=\"topic\">\r\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\">Multi-Organization View in Security Cloud Control</h1>\r\n<div class=\"body taskbody\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">The Security Cloud Control multi-organization view is designed for enterprises that need to manage multiple\r\n            organizations for a single company, and for Managed Service Providers who need to manage\r\n            multiple organizations for different companies.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p\">In a multi-organization view there is a \"manager organization\" and there are \"managed organizations\". Use the manager organization to administer and configure both the manager organization and some aspects of managed organizations. These are some of the administrative tasks you can perform from the manager organization: </p>\r\n<ul class=\"ul\">\r\n<li class=\"li\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">Configure role-based access control (RBAC) for the manager and managed\r\n                    organizations. You can define users and groups in the manager organization and permit them to access different managed organization as well as define their level of administrative access to a product.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"li\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">Provision product subscriptions for the manager organization and distribute subscription entitlements from the manager organization to the managed organizations associated with it.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"li\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">Like a managed organization, the manager organization can claim and verify an email domain for your organization in Security Cloud Control. This step is required for integrating an identity provider with Security\r\n                    Cloud Sign On. It also enables organization administrators to reset user\r\n                    passwords or modify multifactor authentication settings in the claimed\r\n                    domain.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"li\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">Like a managed organization, the manager organization can integrate identity providers with Security Cloud Sign-On using Security\r\n                    Assertion Markup Language (SAML) to provide SSO to the users of your\r\n                    organization.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li class=\"li\">\r\n<p class=\"p\">Review manager user activity in the audit log.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"p\">The \"Security Cloud Control Multi-Organizations\" administrator guide explains\r\n            multi-organizations and how to perform various tasks in a manager organization. It is a supplement to \" <a data-scope=\"external\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://securitydocs.cisco.com/api/v0/apps?appId=SccPlatform&amp;topic=welcome_scc\" title=\"\">Cisco Security Cloud Control Administration Guide</a>.\"</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</article>\r\n","ditaVal":"","format":"html"},"bookTitle":{"value":""},"shortDescription":{"value":""}}},"parameters":{"appId":"SccMultiorgAdmin","topicAlias":"about-scc-multiorg"}}